&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Own the product definition and delivery of Garage Hub&#39;s and Driveline&#39;s core distribution platform capabilities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Design and evolve systems that support order management, catalog ingestion, part normalization, and data quality across customers and suppliers, including UX/UI where applicable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Partner with Engineering to plan and deliver product releases that support customer and distributor workflows and scale.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Work closely with Operations and Strategic Partnerships teams to understand distribution-specific constraints (shipping logic, catalog complexity, pricing rules, inventory data, supplier variability) and translate them into product requirements.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Partner directly with Operations to identify and resolve pain points, validate requirements, and ensure solutions are practical and adopted in live operating environments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: Operations Clerk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A bit about us:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re on a mission to change the tire industry — how it’s delivered and how it’s experienced.&amp;nbsp; A pioneer in the automotive e-commerce industry, we take pride in our extensive selection of top-name brands and budget-friendly options, ensuring our customers find the perfect tire to suit their needs. As a part of our growing and dynamic team, you&#39;ll contribute to our commitment to exceptional service, innovation, and customer satisfaction. Embrace the opportunity to be a driving force behind one of the fastest growing e-commerce companies in the US and apply now!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A bit more about this role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Operations Clerk executes core operational functions that are key in the day-to-day operations of the company. Sitting at the intersection of external suppliers and internal teams, the operations clerk helps to quarterback a variety of tasks across divisions. Tasks include, but are not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contacting suppliers for order updates and cancellations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring orders are being shipped and delivered in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitoring shipping status and investigating lost, missing, or damaged packages.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eligibility Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Available to work full shifts till 5pm PST&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must not have had any disciplinary actions regarding attendance, conduct and/or performance in the past 90 days, and must not be approaching such action.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self motivated to get your tasks done timely&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be fluent in speaking, reading, and writing English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities will include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling suppliers and getting status of past due orders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Processing cancellation requests from the customer service team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Processing FedEx missing tire cases and performing investigations, when needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Processing sales orders for Tires-Easy owned locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performing inventory audit trails and adjustments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Being available on phones for warehouse questions regarding orders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist our Strategic Partnership Director with onboarding of new suppliers and other tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attributes to success:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tenacity and follow up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication is key both externally to suppliers and internally among coworkers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired skills &amp;amp; experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Google Suite products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in data processing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High speed Wi-Fi connection at home office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent professional communication skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re a great team member with a can-do attitude; you’re self- reflective&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or equivalent preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please submit resume in English.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Partnerships Analyst&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A bit about us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re on a mission to change the tire industry — how it’s delivered and how it’s experienced. A pioneer in automotive e-commerce, we take pride in our extensive selection of top-name brands and budget-friendly options, ensuring our customers find the perfect tire for their needs. As part of our growing team across the US and Argentina, you’ll contribute to our commitment to exceptional service, innovation, and customer satisfaction. We’re one of the fastest growing e-commerce companies in the US — come help us build it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A bit more about this role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a sales role. There are no quotas, no prospecting, no cold outreach. This is an execution and analysis role supporting strategic partnerships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will operate as the analytical and operational backbone for our account lead — drafting their communications, building weekly presentations, tracking every open commitment, and making sure nothing falls through the cracks. The person in this seat is the one who makes the partnership look sharp from the outside. You work in the background and take pride in that.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work in an entrepreneurial environment where we are constantly looking to learn what our partners need and to develop better ways to serve them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eligibility Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent command of the English language — written and verbal. This is the single most important requirement for this role. You will be assessed on it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Finished university degree in Economics, Finance, Mathematics, Engineering, Statistics, Computer Science, or a similarly rigorous field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Availability to work full US business hours (PST)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 2–4 years of full-time private sector experience in a role requiring both analytical output and professional written communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must not have had any disciplinary actions regarding attendance, conduct, and/or performance in the past 90 days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities will include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft all written communications for the account lead — emails, formal responses, and internal updates — requiring minimal revision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain weekly account presentations, pulling data and shaping it into a clear, executive-ready narrative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor account performance metrics and proactively surface anomalies or risks before they escalate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track all open action items and commitments; drive them to closure without being asked&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare briefing materials ahead of every meeting or call&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate rapid internal responses to partner requests, managing timelines and follow-through&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pull and analyze data from internal systems (BigQuery, dashboards) to answer business questions and build the fact base for strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clean log of all partner commitments, decisions, and status updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attributes to success:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a precise, professional writer in English — your drafts do not need to be cleaned up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are uncomfortable when something is unresolved or overdue; you close loops&lt;/li&gt;
